issue.title: Extensionification: All blocks should be implemented using extension system
issue.body:
# Extensionification!

## Goals

- All blocks in Scratch 3.0 should be entirely defined within `scratch-vm`. Adding a new block should not require modifications in `scratch-gui` or `scratch-blocks`.
- All blocks in Scratch 3.0 should be implemented in the same way. We should not maintain two (or more) different ways to define blocks.
- The extension system should be enhanced such that it becomes powerful enough to implement every existing Scratch 3.0 block.

## Tasks

* Supporting features
  * [x] Extensions should be able to place buttons in the toolbox
  * [ ] Extension blocks should refresh when changing targets
  * [ ] Extension blocks should refresh on certain actions (create/update/delete variable, list, procedure, message, etc.)
  * [ ] Extensionified categories can be interleaved with categories defined in `scratch-gui`'s `makeToolboxXML`
* Serialization
  * [ ] Existing SB3 files, including those containing variables, lists, or custom procedures, can be loaded correctly when those categories are extensionified.
  * [ ] An SB3 file saved with extensionified variables, lists, or custom procedures can be loaded correctly in an older editor (esp. Scratch Desktop).
* Categories
  * [ ] Motion
  * [ ] Looks
  * [ ] Sound
  * [ ] Events (including `broadcast _` & friends)
  * [ ] Control (including `stop _`)
  * [ ] Sensing (including `_ of _`)
  * [ ] Operators
  * [ ] Variables
  * [ ] My Blocks
